text: Presidential elections were held in Austria on 9 October 2022. Current President Alexander Van der Bellen from the Greens was able to run for one more term. About 6.36 million voting-age citizens were eligible to vote. Final results showed that Van der Bellen was re-elected in the first round with 57% of the vote. Van der Bellen won in all of the 116 administrative districts of Austria. ==References== Category:October 2022 events Category:2022 elections in Europe Category:2022 in Austria Category:Politics of Austria
title: 2022 Austrian presidential election
